  "text": "In vitro fatty acid uptake study with HuTu-80 cells. The human intestinal epithelial cell line, HuTu-80 cells (Cell Lines Service, Eppelheim, Germany) transfected with human SGLT-1 [CITATION_1] , was used in the present study. Cells were seeded into 12-well plates at 5 ϫ 10 5 cells/well and grown to 95-100% confluence. The cells were then cultured in glucose-and FBS-free DMEM for 1 h before oleate uptake. Cells were washed twice with Dulbecco's PBS (DPBS) (GIBCO, Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA) and then incubated in DPBS containing CaCl2 (1.8 mM) and MgCl2 (1 mM) [PBS (ϩ)] buffer with or without 0.5 mM SSO for 1 h at 37°C. To determine the effects of CA on oleate uptake, cells were incubated in PBS (ϩ) buffer containing [ 3 H]oleate (cat. no. NET289, 0.14 M, 1 Ci/ml; PerkinElmer, Tokyo, Japan), 50 M oleate, 1% TO, and 0.2% BSA with or without 2 mM of CA for 30 min at 37°C. The cells were then washed three times with DPBS and solubilized with 0.5 ml of 0.1 N NaOH. A total of 10 ml of Scintillation Cocktail (Hionic-Fluor, PerkinElmer) was added to the resultant cell lysate. The radioactivity of 3 H in the cell lysate was measured using an automatic liquid scintillation spectrometer (Tri-Carb 2550 TR/LL, Packard, Rungis, France).",
